    "body": "## Summary\n\nNeovim's bundled cucumber filetype plugin (`runtime/ftplugin/cucumber.vim`) contains the\nsame code injection vulnerability as vim < 9.2.0496 (GHSA-4473-94jm-w5x9).\n\nThe `s:stepmatch()` function uses `Kernel.eval()` to compile a step-definition regex\npattern into a Ruby `Regexp` object. If the pattern in a malicious `.rb` step-definition\nfile contains embedded Ruby code (e.g., via `#{}` interpolation), it is executed when\nthe user uses Neovim's jump-to-definition feature on a `.feature` file.\n\n## Affected Code\n\n`runtime/ftplugin/cucumber.vim`, line 98-99 (last vim-patch: 2023-06-11):\n\n```vim\nif has(\"ruby\") && pattern !~ '\\\\\\@<!#{'\n  ruby VIM.command(\"return #{if (begin; Kernel.eval('/'+VIM.evaluate('pattern')+'/'); rescue SyntaxError; end) === VIM.evaluate('a:target') then 1 else 0 end}\")\n```\n\n`pattern` comes from `matchstr(line, step_pattern)` where `line` is read from step-definition\n`.rb` files via `readfile(file)`. A malicious step pattern like:\n\n```ruby\n/#{`id > /tmp/pwned`}/\n```\n\nwill cause `Kernel.eval('/#{`id > /tmp/pwned`}/')` to execute a shell command when the\nuser jumps to the step definition using `[<C-D>` or `<C-W>d`.\n\n## Conditions\n\n- The user must have Ruby available as a Nvim provider (`has(\"ruby\")` is true)\n- The user must be editing a `.feature` (Cucumber) file\n- A malicious `.rb` step-definition file must be accessible under `b:cucumber_steps_glob`\n  (default: `features/**/*.rb` relative to the feature file)\n\n## Upstream Fix\n\nThe vim fix for GHSA-4473-94jm-w5x9 (vim >= 9.2.0496) replaces `Kernel.eval` with\n`Regexp.new()`:\n\n```vim\nruby VIM.command(\"return #{Regexp.new(VIM.evaluate('pattern')) === VIM.evaluate('a:target') ? 1 : 0}\")\n```\n\nThis avoids arbitrary code execution by using the safe `Regexp.new()` constructor\ninstead of `Kernel.eval()` to compile the regex.\n\nNeovim's cucumber.vim (last updated 2023-06-11) predates this fix.\n\n## References\n\n- Upstream vim advisory: https://github.com/vim/vim/security/advisories/GHSA-4473-94jm-w5x9\n- Affects Vim < 9.2.0496\n- MacVim issue: https://github.com/macvim-dev/macvim/issues/1654\n",
